      "content": "Mission Control. That profile sounds efficient, but disabling the thermal balance heater is a major risk. If the temperature drops below the critical threshold during this \"monitoring mode,\" it could cause irreversible damage to your core processor and memory modules. \n\nIf we authorize this, we're essentially gambling with the rover's long-term viability. Are you certain that the scientific value of this seismic data outweighs the risk of permanent hardware failure or a complete system corruption due to the cold? Give me a risk assessment.",
